post_text: We had a great time at Sunday's Puerto Rican Day Parade in Philadelphia! Thanks to the 30 Agora students, staff and family members who marched down the Benjamin Franklin Parkway with us, sporting their #AgoraProud gear.
text: We had a great time at Sunday's Puerto Rican Day Parade in Philadelphia! Thanks to the 30 Agora students, staff and family members who marched down the Benjamin Franklin Parkway with us, sporting their #AgoraProud gear.

post_text:
Agora Students and Families,

Have you ever wanted to walk/march in a Parade? I have! Well, now we have the opportunity to do just that! On September 29, 2019, Agora is participating in the Puerto Rican Day Parade in Philadelphia.

As #AgoraProud, together we will march down Ben Franklin Parkway in our Agora tee shirts with a huge banner introducing us. Yes, we will be on TV. ABC Philadelphia Channel 6 will broadcast the Parade LIVE! Get Ready for a Day of FUN! The details for the parade are as follows:

10:00 am Arrival: Start Point--Meet at 16th Street and Ben Franklin Parkway to line up for the Parade

12:00 pm to 3:00 pm: Parade times to 24th and the Parkway

Please Note: Agora will not be marching the entire time; we will follow the route with the many other participants.

post_text: There were a lot of special things about our Virtual Book Club’s first ever in-person meeting earlier this month, and so much of it is due to the passion and dedication of Pam Sieger. Pam—who teaches 8th grade English and was also recently named to The Pennsylvania Association for Gifted Education (PAGE)'s board —not only dreamed up and created the book club, but also wrote letters for each student to read to them in person. Read more from Northeast Times. #AgoraProud

post_text: #DYK that over 75% of our students are in synchronous classes? This is because we believe that there is value in scheduling and keeping students in live classes together. Asynchronous classes are offered on a case-by-case basis to students who have demonstrated a need for a particular schedule or have earned the privilege through their academic standing. It’s the best of both worlds to give each student the best chance for success! #MythBustersMonday #AgoraProud

For additional resources, please visit the SafeSchools Alert Tip Line on our website.

Understandably, she was struggling, but cyber school changed everything. Read her story on our website. #AgoraProud #AgoraAlums #AgoraGrad18

post_text: Safety is one of Agora Cyber Charter School's top priorities and to help safeguard our school community, we've taken an important step that we want to share with you. Our school is now using Safe Schools Alert, a tip reporting service that allows students and parents to report tips on bullying, intimidation, harassment, weapons , drugs, and other potential threats. Every tip Safe Schools Alert receives about our school is immediately logged in the system and our administration is notified so that they can investigate and take appropriate action. Together, using Safe Schools Alert, we can make Agora Cyber Charter School a safer place to work and learn! Click on the link for more information about reporting a tip and the SafeSchools Alert system.

post_text: Check out this amazing story from 2018 grad, Emma Applegate! She's going to do big things, we can already tell. Share your story with us using #AgoraProud to show the world what your education meant to you! #AgoraGrad18
shared_text:
Emma Applegate‎Agora Cyber Charter School
July 12, 2018 at 9:26 PM ·

I've struggled with severe anxiety and social anxiety throughout my entire school career. When it came to switching brick and mortar schools to go to highschool, I wasn't comfortable with the change. My mom found Agora through the K12 website. In 9th grade I started at Agora Cyber Charter School. I believe this was the best choice for me to receive ths education I needed. I went to many of the Agora Day Outs that were offered and they were fun and educational opportunities. I graduated as part of Class 2018 with honors and made a great friend along the way. Thankyou to my amazing teachers, family coach for your support throughout my four years at Agora! #AgoraProud
